terms.medium_def:
The Deity; 
called LORD or LORD (KJV= Jehovah) (יהוה); or LORD (KJV= Jehovah) (יְהֹוִה); or LORD (יָהּ); or Lord (אֲדֹנָי); or God (KJV= Elohim) (אֱלֹהִים); or Baal (KJV= Baali; NIV= Master) (בַּעֲלִי); or Almighty (שַׁדַּי); or Most High (עַל); or Most High (Aramiac עִלַּי); or Most High (KJV= "most High") or Most High (KJV= Highest) (עֶלְיוֹן); or Most High (Aramiac עֶלְיוֹן); or God/ Most High (KJV= "most high God") (אֵל עֶלְיוֹן); or God (אֵל=God); or El/-Elohe (אֵל אֱלֹהִים); or El/-Elohe Israel (=Alt tag) (אֵל אֱלֹהֵי יִשְׂרָאֵל); or Banner (KJV= Nissi) (נֵס); or Banner (KJV= Nissi) (=Alt tag) (יְהֹוָה נִסִּי); or Peace (KJV= Shalom) (שָׁלוֹם); or Peace (KJV= Shalom) (=Alt tag) (יְהֹוָה שָׁלוֹם); or Provider (KJV= Jireh) (יִרְאֶה); or Provider (KJV= Jireh) (=Alt tag) (יִרְאֶה); or LORD our Righteousness (NIV= Righteous Saviour) (צִדְקֵנוּ); or LORD our Righteousness (NIV= Righteous Saviour) (יְהֹוָה צִדְקֵנוּ (=Alt tag)); or Everlasting (NIV= Eternal) (עוֹלָם); or Jealous (קַנָּא); or Hosts (NIV= Almighty) (צָבָא); or Highest (ὕψιστος); or "hosts" (KJV= "sabaoth;" NIV= Almighty) (σαβαώθ); or Abba (ἀββά); or Eli (ἠλί); or Eloi (ἐλωΐ) §(Lord will) Provide, cause to be seen.
This name means to see, look at, inspect, look after

Jacob's son who founded the tribe of Reuben living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.29.32; 
referred to as Reuben or Reubenite (רְאוּבֵן), or Reubenite or Reuben (רְאוּבֵנִי), or Reuben (Ῥουβήν); 
son of Israel and Leah; 
a brother of Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun and Dinah; 
half-brother of: Dan, Naphtali, Gad, Asher, Joseph and Benjamin; 
father of Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron and Carmi.

Jacob's son who founded the tribe of Reuben living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.29.32; 
referred to as Reuben or Reubenite (רְאוּבֵן), or Reubenite or Reuben (רְאוּבֵנִי), or Reuben (Ῥουβήν); 
son of Israel and Leah; 
a brother of Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun and Dinah; 
half-brother of: Dan, Naphtali, Gad, Asher, Joseph and Benjamin; 
father of Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron and Carmi. § Reubenite, of Reuben "behold a son"
a descendant of Reuben the son of Jacob

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.37.13; 
only referred to as Irijah (יִרְאִיָּיה); 
a son of Shelemiah. § son of Shelemiah, a captain of the guard who arrested Jeremiah

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.2.52; 
referred to as Haroeh (רֹאֶה), or Reaiah (רְאָיָה); 
a son of Shobal; 
father of Jahath. § a man of Judah

A man from the tribe of Reuben living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.5.5; 
only referred to as Reaiah (רְאָיָה); 
a son of Micah; 
father of Baal.

